HEADWORD: Manganate
<hw>Man"ga*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>manganate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt of manganic
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The manganates are usually green, and are well-known
compounds, though derived from a hypothetical acid.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

